DESCRIPTION:Roger Rey raced alongside the great names of Formula 1. At eighty-four\, his wife Marylou asks him to return to racing in honour of their late son. After a series of chaotic beginnings\, Roger rediscovers the thrill of adrenaline when\, without warning\, Marylou is hospitalized and passes away. On her deathbed\, she makes him promise to take part in a major European hill climb in her honour. At nearly ninety years old\, Roger has nothing left to lose and sets out to challenge age\, fear\, and death.
